{
  "number": 286,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/286",
  "title": "refactor: autoHide should be a widget shared behavior, not a component one",
  "body": "The way [autoHide is written](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/7f983d0d6c592de6a091ec2dc5b5df57da151a82/decorators/autoHide.js) is \"broken\".\n\nIt's acknowledging that the React Components are aware of the node they are mounted to (container). While they should not know about it.\n\nIt complexifies the implementation of the autoHide feature for nothing nad restrict us to use it on widgets that are bound to react only.\n\nWe should move this decorator as a \"widget\" decorator (shared behavior). And maybe do the right thing => move the decorator call outside of the widget.\n",
  "created_at": "2015-10-19T17:21:44Z",
